                <td valign="top" class="row1"> <span class="smalltext"><b>Nostalgia</b></span>
                  <p><span class="largetext">It is a late night in the cold month of January, I found myself wandering alone, seemingly lost of void and cause.  The guild hall was quiet as it has been of late, with the exception of a couple Knights (The Rogue Gryph and the Ranger Ken) laying destruction in CoM. Stumbling forward as if I was still trapped in that cold crypt The Undertaker put me in.
<br />

<br />
I finally look up and found myself standing before a very old yet familiar sight.  A large chessboard in the looming cold mountains of Butcherblock.  I remember being here in my 7th season as a Paladin of Brell surronded by friends, comrades, mentors in arms.  Yet here it is 51 season's later in this Paladin's life and I feel all alone standing before a ruin of a landmark of the glory days of Butcherblock.
<br />

<br />
I slowly sit down hearing more bones creak than my own armor and think about the three friends I traveled the world with in those younger days.  That beautiful lass with the fiery red locks, whom I envisioned a Crown upon her head has become a Queen just like I witnessed in my dream.  And yet politics and responsibility has seperated us from our days of great adventures.  That fun loving drunk little gnome who brought laughter to my eyes and ears disappeared on us well over 20 seasons ago. Although I have seen and heard a ghost here lately in the halls of the guild castle that sounds so much like me drunk little friend, it brings a smile to me face.  My lord Mentor through his destruction of Unrest gathered a strong following and tho his heart and foundation will always be a KoA he went on to lead his own army in the CoF.
<br />

<br />
And so I sit here me Queen with tears in me eyes and think about all the Knights who have come and gone, of Knights that we have lost who themselves no longer Adventure in the world of Norrath.  But most of all I sit here under this old tall tree at the chessboard and dream of the days of adventure and glory, when the hustle and bustle of the Wayfarer's camp could not be heard.  When a young brash dwarf who was so full of himself and sure of his purpose met three of the greatest Adventurers he ever traveled Norrath with.  Ahhh the golden age is gone, I could easily sit here in nostalgia and die an old forgotten dwarven paladin and yet.....
<br />

<br />
I get to my feet. I secure my shield to my left arm. The sound of my well oiled sword slides free from my scabbard.  I scan the chessboard with that gleam of the once lost young brash dwarf and wonder. "How the hell do these damn Undead keep coming back to this chessboard?"
<br />

<br />
Off in the far distance at the Wayfarer's camp the hustle and bustle of the adventurer's there slowly gets quiet, as one by one each adventurer turns towards the direction of the chessboard.  A few seconds goes by and the noise of the camp starts to rise again as the adventurers return to their tasks.  But not a one of them forgets to quickly, the loud cry of "LONG LIVE THE KOA!" and the dwarven laughter that followed.<br />_________________<br />My Queen I will gladly escort you where ever your paths may take you. My sword and my life are at your disposal and I pledge that upon my death your life will never be taken while I stand watch 
<br />

<br />
Long Live the KoA
<br />
Zabor Queensguard
<br />
General of the KoA</span><span class="smalltext"></span></p>
                </td>
