                <td width="186" valign="top" class="row1" nowrap> <span class="largetext"><a name="4243"></a><b>Banaclur</b></span><br>
                  <span class="smalltext">Friend or Foe?!?!<br>
                  <br>
                  <br>
                  Joined: 20 Mar 2003<br>
                  Posts: 0<br>
                  </span></td>
                <td valign="top" class="row1"> <span class="smalltext"><b>memories</b></span>
                  <p><span class="largetext">An old dwarf sits in the courtyard of unrest.
<br />
His eyes have an infinite gaze as he looks at the undead wandering.
<br />
A lonely tear runs down the folds of his face until it disappears in his now grey beard.
<br />

<br />
His mind wanders on days passed.
<br />
It returns to his home town the idealistic young dwarf leaving the safety of his home to wander Butcher Block Mountains.
<br />
Encountering many more experienced people who scorn him and tell him that he should be much more experienced before he can join their circle and guilds.
<br />
Then he makes his vow to never join them but to make his own.
<br />

<br />
The young dwarf steps are confident and he ends up at the chest board.
<br />
He battles the skeletons there and life is wonderfull and full of awe and wonder.
<br />
There he first laid eyes on the hesitant elf female she gets into trouble and he steps in and together they slay the too big a foe for each seperate.
<br />
They start to talk and connect at some level and decide to venture together.
<br />

<br />
A sigh leaves the old dwarfs lips so many lost so many left behind. He shakes his head at the strange curves that life has lead him on his path.
<br />
So much left not understood so much not solved. Choices made and choices forced on him. He takes his head into his hands as if it is too heavy to wear just on his neck. 
<br />

<br />
Then a faint smile visits his face for he recollects the odd gnome who soon after the two had joined met them. A beer in his hand and a swift blade drawn when the others didn't think he could stand on two feet let alone lay a foe with that. The crude humor they had soon grown fond of and the restless spirit within him to urge him to lead them to new and strange places.
<br />

<br />
Where is that gnome now? Is he still alive? The old dwarf doesn't know lately he is wandering about all those he left behind. He coughs to clear his throat and has to take a deep breath to put the grief behind bars again.
<br />
He straightens his back and regains composure. 
<br />

<br />
Then he is reminded of that not so much younger dwarf that joins the three at the chessboard. The younger dwarf somehow looks up at him although he cannot find the reason for he, although he tried to be more experienced, was far from a seasoned veteran at that time.
<br />
In his enthusiasm and the formal way he addressed him the old dwarf was many times humbled. Although the younger dwarf insisted that he was his mentor it certainly wasn't clear most of the time who was the teacher and who the student.
<br />

<br />
A smile breaks through on his face as the old dwarf remembers his old friend in younger days. Although their paths had some of the time deviated the friendship forged then was never defeated and has stood fast as only two paladins true at heart can have. Fortunately some of the time the two have been still side by side battling mostly against the odds but always true at heart and no quarter will be given and none was ever asked. Ah when a dwarf has made at least one true friend then his life was not in vain.
<br />

<br />
His mind wanders now to the time when he started to talk to the others to make their own guild. At first is was a thought discarded for it was a too tall idea for the others but he didn't let off he kept bringing the subject before them. At last they got help from a much more experienced elf an zcquaintance of the gnome who knew more on what it took to make theri own guild. By that time they had started to venture forth to other places and seldom returned to Biutcher Block mountains for they had become more experienced and the gnome had led them to many strange area trying their steel and witt. The young dwarf had for some time called their group the Knights of Areilla and they had grown accustomed to fight for her honor and so the name of the guild was fast decided to be just that. The gnome would be the first to lead them into battle and after a while areilla felt the courage to lead them herself. Ah those were good times.
<br />

<br />
The old dwarf stands up and looks at his armor checking if all is fast and sturdy. He knows that he had to leave that guild because staying is not always the best choice for what had been build would have been torn apart if he had stayed.
<br />
But for the sake of old days he draws his sword and once more the freight of many foe in unrest is awakened when he charges forward with the familar cry...
<br />

<br />
"KNIGHTS OF AREILLA To SERVE or DIE!!!!"<br />_________________<br />Banaclur
<br />
Honor is not an option, it is a given</span><span class="smalltext"></span></p>
